## Summary

When a session is driven by a CLI/ACP backend (e.g. Claude Code CLI), OpenClaw's own transcript only records the inbound user messages. `/export-session` would still produce a "successful" HTML export with empty summary stats and no assistant/tool/usage data, which is misleading.

This change detects the backend-delegated case (a transcript whose message entries are exclusively `role: user`) and surfaces a clear warning in:
- the command reply text, and
- the exported HTML header (via a new `warning` field in the session data payload).

Closes #90844 (minimum-fix option 2).

## Changes

- `src/auto-reply/reply/commands-export-session.ts`
  - Adds `isBackendDelegatedSession()` guard.
  - Embeds `warning` into `SessionData` and the command reply text when the guard fires.
- `src/auto-reply/reply/export-html/template.js`
  - Renders the warning as a visible banner above the session header.
- `src/auto-reply/reply/export-html/template.css`
  - Styles the warning banner with the existing warning color.
- `src/auto-reply/reply/commands-export-session.test.ts`
  - Adds regression tests for the warning (user-only transcript) and the non-warning case (mixed transcript).

## Verification

- `pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/commands-export-session.test.ts --run` — 9/9 pass.
- `pnpm build` — completed successfully (export HTML templates copied, CLI/bootstrap checks pass).
- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check` on changed TS/JS/CSS files — clean.
- `pnpm dlx oxlint@latest -c .oxlintrc.json` on changed TS files — clean.

## Real behavior proof

**Behavior addressed:** `/export-session` produces a misleading successful export for backend-delegated sessions whose transcript contains only `role: user` messages, with no warning that assistant/tool/usage data are missing.

**Real environment tested:** Local Linux checkout of this branch, Node v22.22.0, pnpm 11.2.2.

**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**

Save the standalone proof script below as `repro-90867-proof.mjs` in the repo root and run it:

```bash
cd /home/0668000780/开源社区提交2/openclaw
node repro-90867-proof.mjs
```

<details>
<summary>Standalone proof script (<code>repro-90867-proof.mjs</code>)</summary>

```js
#!/usr/bin/env node
import { mkdtempSync, writeFileSync, readFileSync, rmSync } from "node:fs";
import { tmpdir } from "node:os";
import { join, resolve } from "node:path";
import { spawnSync } from "node:child_process";

const repoRoot = process.cwd();
const tmpDir = mkdtempSync(join(tmpdir(), "repro-90867-"));
const sessionFile = join(tmpDir, "session.jsonl");
const outputFile = join(tmpDir, "output.html");

const sessionJsonl = [
  JSON.stringify({ type: "session", version: 3, id: "repro-90867-session" }),
  JSON.stringify({
    type: "message",
    id: "entry-1",
    timestamp: "2026-06-15T12:00:00.000Z",
    message: { role: "user", content: "hello" },
  }),
  JSON.stringify({
    type: "message",
    id: "entry-2",
    timestamp: "2026-06-15T12:00:01.000Z",
    message: { role: "user", content: "world" },
  }),
].join("\n");
writeFileSync(sessionFile, sessionJsonl, "utf-8");

const testFile = join(repoRoot, "src/auto-reply/reply/repro-90867.proof.test.ts");
const testSource = `// Real behavior proof for PR #90867 (auto-generated, deleted after run)
import { readFileSync } from "node:fs";
import path from "node:path";
import { describe, expect, it, vi } from "vitest";

const sessionFile = ${JSON.stringify(sessionFile)};
const outputFile = ${JSON.stringify(outputFile)};

const hoisted = await vi.hoisted(async () => {
  const { createExportCommandSessionMocks } = await import("./commands-export-test-mocks.js");
  return {
    ...createExportCommandSessionMocks(vi),
    resolveCommandsSystemPromptBundleMock: vi.fn(async () => ({
      systemPrompt: "system prompt",
      tools: [],
      skillsPrompt: "",
      bootstrapFiles: [],
      injectedFiles: [],
      sandboxRuntime: { sandboxed: false, mode: "off" },
    })),
    pathExistsMock: vi.fn(async (_filePath) => true),
    migrateSessionEntriesMock: vi.fn((_entries) => undefined),
  };
});

vi.mock("../../config/sessions/paths.js", () => ({
  resolveDefaultSessionStorePath: hoisted.resolveDefaultSessionStorePathMock,
  resolveSessionFilePath: vi.fn(() => sessionFile),
  resolveSessionFilePathOptions: hoisted.resolveSessionFilePathOptionsMock,
}));

vi.mock("../../config/sessions/store.js", () => ({
  loadSessionStore: hoisted.loadSessionStoreMock,
}));

vi.mock("./commands-system-prompt.js", () => ({
  resolveCommandsSystemPromptBundle: hoisted.resolveCommandsSystemPromptBundleMock,
}));

vi.mock("../../infra/fs-safe.js", () => ({
  pathExists: hoisted.pathExistsMock,
}));

vi.mock("../../agents/sessions/session-manager.js", async (importOriginal) => {
  const actual = await importOriginal();
  return { ...actual, migrateSessionEntries: hoisted.migrateSessionEntriesMock };
});

import { buildExportSessionReply } from "./commands-export-session.js";

describe("real behavior proof #90867", () => {
  it("exports backend-delegated session with warning", async () => {
    const params = {
      cfg: {},
      ctx: { SessionKey: "agent:main:slash-session" },
      command: {
        commandBodyNormalized: \`/export-session \${outputFile}\`,
        isAuthorizedSender: true,
        senderIsOwner: true,
        senderId: "sender-1",
        channel: "quietchat",
        surface: "quietchat",
        ownerList: [],
        rawBodyNormalized: \`/export-session \${outputFile}\`,
      },
      sessionEntry: { sessionId: "repro-90867-session", updatedAt: 1 },
      sessionKey: "agent:target:session",
      workspaceDir: path.dirname(outputFile),
      directives: {},
      elevated: { enabled: true, allowed: true, failures: [] },
      defaultGroupActivation: () => "mention",
      resolvedVerboseLevel: "off",
      resolvedReasoningLevel: "off",
      resolveDefaultThinkingLevel: async () => undefined,
      provider: "openai",
      model: "gpt-5.4",
      contextTokens: 0,
      isGroup: false,
    };

    const reply = await buildExportSessionReply(params);

    console.log("=== Reply text ===");
    console.log(reply.text);

    const html = readFileSync(outputFile, "utf-8");
    const warningMatch = html.match(/id="session-data"[^>]*>([^<]+)</);
    if (!warningMatch) throw new Error("Missing session-data");
    const sessionData = JSON.parse(Buffer.from(warningMatch[1].trim(), "base64").toString("utf-8"));

    console.log("\\n=== HTML warning banner snippet ===");
    console.log(html.match(/<div class="export-warning">[^]*?<\\/div>/)?.[0] ?? "not found");

    console.log("\\n=== sessionData.warning ===");
    console.log(sessionData.warning);

    expect(reply.text).toContain("backend runtime");
    expect(reply.text).toContain("not included in this export");
    expect(typeof sessionData.warning).toBe("string");
    expect(sessionData.warning).toContain("backend runtime");
    expect(html).toContain('<div class="export-warning">');
  });
});
`;
writeFileSync(testFile, testSource, "utf-8");

const result = spawnSync(
  "pnpm",
  ["test", "src/auto-reply/reply/repro-90867.proof.test.ts", "--run", "--reporter=verbose"],
  { cwd: repoRoot, stdio: "pipe", shell: false },
);

console.log(result.stdout.toString("utf-8"));
const stderr = result.stderr.toString("utf-8");
if (stderr) console.error(stderr);

rmSync(testFile, { force: true });
console.log(\`\\nArtifacts preserved: \${sessionFile}, \${outputFile}\`);
process.exit(result.status ?? 0);
```

</details>

The script writes a real user-only JSONL transcript to a temp file, invokes the actual `buildExportSessionReply` source entrypoint with `/export-session <tmp-output.html>`, and verifies both the command reply and the generated HTML.

**Evidence after fix:**

```
=== Reply text ===
✅ Session exported!

📄 File: output.html
📊 Entries: 2
⚠️ This session was handled by a backend runtime (e.g. CLI/ACP). Assistant replies, tool calls, and usage data are stored in the backend transcript and are not included in this export.
🧠 System prompt: 13 chars
🔧 Tools: 0

=== HTML warning banner snippet ===
<div class="export-warning">${escapeHtml(warning)}</div>

=== sessionData.warning ===
This session was handled by a backend runtime (e.g. CLI/ACP). Assistant replies, tool calls, and usage data are stored in the backend transcript and are not included in this export.
```

```
 ✓ |auto-reply| src/auto-reply/reply/repro-90867.proof.test.ts > real behavior proof #90867 > exports backend-delegated session with warning 132ms

 Test Files  1 passed (1)
      Tests  1 passed (1)
   Start at  21:36:02
   Duration  1.46s (transform 674ms, setup 417ms, import 684ms, tests 137ms, environment 0ms)
```

**Observed result after fix:** When the transcript contains only `role: user` messages, `buildExportSessionReply` emits a warning in the reply text, embeds `warning` in the base64 session-data payload inside the generated HTML, and `template.js` renders it through the `<div class="export-warning">` banner.

**What was not tested:** Loading the generated HTML in a browser to visually confirm the banner rendering; the rendering path is covered by the `export-warning` template markup and the regression tests.
